        "text": "van in",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the last syllable. The verbal root is ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "חָפַשׁ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and occurs once (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 19:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with the Authorized Version rendering \"was free;\" in the same verse is also found a feminine noun derived from it, and rendered in the Authorized Version \"freedom\"). The adjective ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "חָפְשִׁי",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " occurs sixteen times, and is always rendered in the Authorized Version \"free,\" except once \"at liberty\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 34:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The \"freedom\" conveyed by the word is that of ",
        "children": []
