        "class": "accented",
        "text": "separation",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", in the use of it as found here. The leper and the house in which he lived were kept free from contact with others (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Leviticus 13:46",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Gesenius appears, however, to prefer the idea of \"infirmity,\" \"sickness,\" as determining the cast of the meaning of the word in our text, and goes so far as to translate it an \"hospital,\" quoting the word of Suidas, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "τὸ νοσοκομεῖον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
